<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910114-0150</DOCNO><DOCID>910114-0150.</DOCID><HL>   Letters to the Editor:   Ultimate Obscenity</HL><DATE>01/14/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A13</SO><CO>   MDEST</CO><GV>DEFENSE DEPARTMENT (DEF)</GV><LP>   Our government, which protects freedom of religion, isasking its citizens to be ready to fight and possibly die to(among other objectives) protect a country that deniesfreedom of religion from attack by another country of similarphilosophy.   That's bad enough, but the ultimate obscenity is that ourhigh command has cravenly acceded to its client's demandsthat American servicemen and servicewomen neither wearreligious symbols nor hold ceremonies -- including Christmas-- in the open, and that they tear American-flag shoulderpatches from their shirts.</LP><TEXT>   Earl D. Brodie   Lafayette, Calif.</TEXT></DOC>